==English==
===Etymology===
From Hindi/Urdu ''ras'' ([[nectar]] or [[juice]]) and ''malai'' ([[cream]]).

===Noun===
'''ras malai'''

# a sweet dish found in the Indian [[subcontinent]] consisting of sugary cream-colored balls of dough and a creamy sweet liquid, the malai.

